            "content": [
              {
                "nodeType": "text",
                "value": "This character often trips over their own feet, drops things, or fumbles simple tasks like threading a needle or tying a knot. Their lack of dexterity turns even a quiet tavern evening into a minor disaster as they knock over mugs or stumble into furniture. In a village, they\u2019re known as the one who can\u2019t carry eggs without breaking them. It\u2019s not malice\u2014just a complete lack of finesse.",
                "marks": [],
